{"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Notes-on-Conversion","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/ThrowingPropertyWrapper"],"anchor":"Topics"},{"title":"Functions","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/zip(_:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Functions"},{"title":"Operators","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/__(_:_:)-1ova6","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/__(_:_:)-204tb","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/__(_:_:)-4akrm","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/__(_:_:)-52q3f"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Operators"},{"anchor":"Extended-Modules","generated":true,"title":"Extended Modules","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Treat "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" like the throwing property wrappers they are.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"Thrappture","role":"collection","title":"Thrappture","modules":[{"name":"Thrappture"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Property wrappers cannot throw.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are not property wrappers."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This package imagines what life would be like if those statements were not true. 🤩","type":"text"}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"What’s a “Throwing Property Wrapper”?","anchor":"Whats-a-Throwing-Property-Wrapper"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some types are conceptually just wrappers around a value, giving it additional behavior. Swift uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/properties\/#Property-Wrappers"},{"type":"text","text":" to represent these types."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But while throwing errors from properties is supported, throwing errors from a property wrapper’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"wrappedValue","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property, specifically, is not (yet). That’s what a “throwing property wrapper” would employ."}]},{"anchor":"Optional-and-Result-should-be-throwing-property-wrappers","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Optional and Result should be throwing property wrappers."},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" both predate property wrappers, but it’s the right model for them, and we should embrace that as much as possible.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While we can’t actually "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"turn them","type":"text"}]},{"text":" into throwing property wrappers, thinking of them that way enables aids with understanding the helpful utilities found in this package.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Optional","text":"Optional"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" acts ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"halfway"}]},{"text":" to being a property wrapper.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"set"}]}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" an optional to what would be its “"},{"code":"\"wrappedValue","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["var value: Optional = 1","value = 2"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But there is no mechanism in place to assign an optional to an instance of its wrapped value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let newValue: Int = value \/\/ Value of optional type 'Int?' must be unwrapped to a value of type 'Int'"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"And it’s as if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" somehow had an overloaded "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wrappedValue"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"set","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" accessor to match that, because you can also ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"set"}]}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" an optional to be another optional.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["value = .some(3)","value = nil"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Property wrappers deal with that kind of conflation by using ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"projected values","type":"text"}]},{"text":", by way of “","type":"text"},{"code":"$","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"” syntax. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" were a throwing property wrapper, the syntax would be this, instead:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Optional var value = 1","value = 2","$value = .some(3)","$value = nil","let newValue: Int = try value"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"What would that last line throw? ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift\/Optional\/Nil","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional.Nil"}],"overridingTitle":"Optional.Nil"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Result","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Result"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" doesn’t have the conflation problem that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" does, but that’s because it doesn’t offer any syntactic sugar."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" were a throwing property wrapper, the syntax for a “"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" version” of the previous example would be this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@Result<_, Int?.Nil> var value = 1","value = 2","$value = .success(3)","$value = .failure(nil)","let newValue: Int = try value"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Usage Examples","anchor":"Usage-Examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You’ve got the source code, so aside from reading this documentation, see the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Tests","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" folder for example usage! 😺"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/thrappture"]}],"references":{"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/zip(_:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"zip","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<each "},{"text":"Sequence","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">(repeat each "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Sequence"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Sequence","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST"},{"kind":"te